channel.title: Help with objects in client
channel.description: Im a new coder and have looked everywhere on how to solve this and just cant find anything that works. All of my regular trees (object id= 1276) that are already placed are skulls and im trying to figure out how to change them back to regular tree. Any help? Im using a 317 source and client if that helps any. Heres also a picture of what im dealing with. I can just delete them and add different trees but it makes it lagg when i open the client. [img]http://i52.tinypic.com/2cfcvio.jpg[/img]

item.title: Help with objects in client
item.dc:creator: @pepse43 pepse43
item.description:
@pepse43 wrote:

Kidpaparoach:

The ID that was put in was most likely wrong, please check what ID it is by typing ingame ::object or looking on the object list

When i first downloaded the client it was like that when i ran the client. On other clients it shows trees like normal. I just want it to run on this client because when i run on other clients the character is all f’ed up. I thought it would have something to do with custom objects that were added to the client but i checked them and there weren’t any custom object int in the class. Would it might me a model that was added?
